This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents a novel method for motion segmentation using sets of features in the image. It also involves comparing its approach with several state-of-the-art methods in the field of computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as Random Voting (RV) method, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The use of feature-set affinities instead of pair-wise affinities between all features suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper also involves addressing challenges encountered by using previously suggested approaches, which suggests that it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves experiments and comparisons with state-of-the-art methods, which suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
